<plot>A portrait of a coffee-house performer, Little White Lines takes a brutally honest look at the life of Travis Bilenski, a singer-songwriter from Northern California, who risks everything for his music. Exposed and living for the moment, the documentary contrasts his original music with his viewpoint on life, allowing a unique vantage point into the man and his music.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?338590</url></doc>
